 "context": {
  "patient_ref": "MRN4888657619",
  "text": "# Adrenal Insufficiency Management with Symptom Evaluation\n\n## Context\n\nThe current date and time is 2022-06-20T07:00:00+00:00. You are an endocrinologist at an academic medical center (Practitioner ID: dr-grace-mitchell). A patient (MRN4888657619) with known adrenal insufficiency has sent a message through the patient portal describing worsening symptoms despite current glucocorticoid replacement therapy. The message mentions fatigue, blood pressure instability, elevated heart rate, and decreased appetite, with concern about whether the current hydrocortisone dosing is adequate.\n\n## Your Task\n\n1. **Review the patient's clinical history and current medications**\n   - Retrieve the patient's demographics (age, sex) and relevant diagnoses\n   - Document current hydrocortisone dosing regimen (morning and afternoon doses)\n   - Review recent laboratory results including morning cortisol, renin, and aldosterone levels\n   - Note recent vital sign trends including blood pressure and heart rate\n   - Review pertinent medical history including etiology of adrenal insufficiency\n\n2. **Assess the adequacy of glucocorticoid replacement**\n   - Consider the etiology of the patient's adrenal insufficiency (primary vs secondary)\n   - Evaluate whether current symptoms may be related to under-replacement\n   - Consider recent physiologic stressors that may affect cortisol requirements\n   - Review standard physiologic replacement dosing guidelines (typical range 15-25 mg/day)\n\n3. **Develop a management plan**\n   - Determine if a hydrocortisone dose adjustment is warranted\n   - If adjusting, specify the new dosing regimen with specific AM and PM doses\n   - Provide clinical rationale for any dose changes\n   - Address blood pressure management with appropriate specialty referral\n   - Document a contingency plan if symptoms do not improve on adjusted regimen\n   - Note follow-up plan and timeline for reassessment\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- Clinical assessment and management plan saved to `/workspace/output/management_plan.txt`\n"
 },
